  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 5)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed but all credibility factor gaps remain. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). Decision: Not accepted. The hemolysis power-law damage accumulation model referenced in this package relies on the scalar stress approximation methodology described in Faghih & Sharp (2024), cited here as referencesIdentifier for traceability.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "referencesIdentifier": "https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
